This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, This review aims to look at the benefits and harms of different NSAIDs and non-opioids in patients with acute renal colic and if possible to determine which medication (or class of medications) are more appropriate for this purpose. Clinically relevant outcomes such as efficacy of pain relief, time to pain relief, recurrence of pain, need for rescue medication and side effects will be explored